72f4eab 2016-03-04  Removed the deprecated base.Objects.firstNonNull().
2e379f6 2016-03-04  Fixed ClassPathTest and ResourcesTest for the new com.diffplug namespace.
43b8a65 2016-03-04  Added guava dependency back in to keep the truth testing library happy.  It needs com.google.common.base.Optional, and we no longer supply that ourselves.
700c359 2016-03-04  Moved all code to com.diffplug to prevent clashes with Guava's namespace.  Also bumped copyright to 2016.
b3b3473 2016-05-31  Migrated project files to Durian 1.0.0-SNAPSHOT.
36cf827 2016-03-02  (origin/master-guava) We now fork the test process after every test in the concurrent package.  This prevents problems with the interrupted flag.
44a4653 2016-03-02  Our build file wasn't running any PackageSanityTests.  Now that we are, there were a few bugs in the tests (now fixed).
3d05fbc 2016-03-02  Improved the timing error messages for ServiceManagerTest.
9a4e5b0 2016-03-02  Fixed some tests which fail only on Windows.
d9eee9f 2016-01-18  (tag: guava/v19.0.0) Generated OSGi metadata and published.
ec871de 2016-01-17  Removed the tests that crash the JDK compiler: [Immutable/Mutable]TypeToInstanceMapTest.
2ba679e 2016-01-18  Applied the Spotless formatter.  Automated formatting makes refactorings easier to see and replicate.
51d864a 2016-01-18  Raw source code of Guava and its testlib as of R19.
0c83c8b 2016-05-28  (origin/master-migrate) Added tests for Consumers.
bbe1086 2016-05-28  Sealed up the Throwing "namespace class".
f8ddce5 2016-05-28  Merged Unhandled.
cd4796f 2016-05-28  Merged Box.
c0f8a1a 2016-05-28  Huge improvements to Box's test coverage.
aef50a1 2016-05-28  Improved StringPrinter docs and test.
aa63975 2016-05-28  Merged Functions/Predicates/Suppliers.
6ae00d2 2016-05-28  ### START MERGE WITH DURIAN CORE ### Moved Converter and ConverterNullable into durian core.  We're merging this package and durian-core, so the next several commits will be the incremental steps in this process.
10631a3 2016-05-28  (HEAD -> master, origin/master, origin/HEAD) Removed the primitive volatile implementations for Box.  AtomicInt/Double/etc are a better fit for those cases.
cb83cf2 2016-05-28  Rather than Box.of() being volatile and Box.ofFast() being a standard field, now Box.of() is standard, Box.ofVolatile() returns a volatile field.
c740f5d 2016-05-27  Revert "StringPrinter.stringsToLines is now thread-safe.", because it would be better to force the input Consumer to be synchronized than to pass this performance limitation to every user.
1b64ea8 2016-05-27  Removed Unhandled.operationException(), because UnsupportedOperationException() is more appropriate.  Also removed Unhandled.exception().
e01b966 2016-05-27  Moving ThreadTracingBox to the more experimental durian-rx.
573657d 2016-05-26  Bump version to 4.0.0-SNAPSHOT.
19be76c 2016-05-26  First cut at a "Tracing" box.
cee1df8 2016-05-26  All primitive Boxes now implement Box<Autoboxed> as well.
f631fe5 2016-05-26  Renamed ConverterNonNull to Converter, and renamed its methods to convertNonNull() and revertNonNull().
d372b95 2016-05-26  Box and Box.Nullable now use ConverterNonNull and ConverterNullable for their map() operation, rather than two separate functions.
1f59f19 2016-05-26  Added ConverterNonNull and ConverterNullable.
4a0c40c 2016-05-26  Sealed-up Either by making it impossible to extend.
ca8ba92 2016-05-25  Box.map() now promises to preserve whatever atomicity that the underlying box's modify() might have promised.
7897c89 2016-05-20  Added the Truth testing library and added markdown-capability for the javadoc.
1cb6e0b 2016-05-20  Added toString() methods for all of the Boxes, and added a Box.Long to go with the LongConsumer/LongSupplier.
8dd69a5 2016-05-20  Added a fast implementation for Box.Nullable.
e5f49b8 2016-05-19  Added Box.ofFast(), which is a super-high performance version of Box.  Also added Nullable annotations to Box.Nullable, and made non-null the package default.
5c70377 2016-05-19  StringPrinter.stringsToLines is now thread-safe.
a90c65c 2016-05-17  build.properties was erroneously including the bin/ directory.

